Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Development Engineer I* position with *Siemens*. I bring over three years of professional experience building production-grade AI services, distributed systems, and cloud-based applications, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY with a 4.0 GPA.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production systems that directly reflect the technical depth this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected production-grade AI services that translate natural-language intents into safe, validated tool calls across 1000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous system design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed systems. I built generative AI solutions using Python and TypeScript, implementing code-generation workflows and API-aware templates that accelerate developer integration with platform APIs. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented comprehensive observability infrastructure using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks to debug services and track quality over time. I also designed concurrent multi-agent orchestration using LangChain and LangGraph, enabling scalable tool execution across complex workflows in cloud services. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-based Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO — giving me direct hands-on experience with cloud-native, multi-environment backend design. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications. Together, these roles have prepared me to write clean, testable, maintainable code for production systems and contribute meaningfully to building intelligent systems that bring generative AI into the physical world.

